news.title: Shriram Properties' appoints Ravindra Kumar Pandey as new CFO
news.para: This appointment follows the recent elevation of Gopalakrishnan J as executive director & group chief executive officer, which left the CFO position vacant. Gopalakrishnan previously held the position of ED & group CFO.

news.title: Builders, financial institutions cautiously optimistic of growth in realty sector: Report
news.para: "While both current and future sentiments remain firmly in the positive zone suggesting a continued belief in the sector's long-term prospects, the scores reflect a more tempered view on recent real estate growth, influenced by election and budget speculations," Knight Frank said.

news.title: Property investment in China falls 10.2% in January-July 2024
news.para: Property sales by floor area in January-July fell 18.6% from a year earlier, compared with a 19.0% slump in January-June, National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data showed on Thursday.

news.title: New home prices in China drops 4.9% in July 2024
news.para: New home prices fell 4.9% from a year earlier, deeper than a 4.5% slide in June, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data. Prices last fell this sharply in June 2015.

news.title: Bengaluru metro phase-III is running right on time
news.para: This route will connect JP Nagar 4th Phase to Kempapura (32.15 km) and will feature 22 stations along the Outer Ring Road (Orange Line). Additionally, it will connect from Hosahalli Station to Sunkadakatte Depot (12.5 km) with nine stations to be constructed.

news.title: Goa's town planning department withdraws approval for 28-villa project in Cavorim
news.para: The TCP had issued a show-cause notice to the builder in July and had directed that ongoing construction be stopped immediately. “The technical clearance issued for proposed construction of residential villas and compound is revoked,” said town planner S P Surlakar.

news.title: Sunteck Realty posts net profit of Rs 22.78 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Sunteck Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 328.01 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 271 per cent from Rs 88.41 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Punjab to drop NOC clause for property registration
news.para: Minister Aman Arora said after the meeting that the govt will work out the modalities of this proposed policy before the chief minister makes the details public.

news.title: Volkswagen India tech arm leases three floors office space in Pune's Hinjewadi
news.para: The company has leased the space spread over more than 1.23 lakh sq ft in Hudson Block forming part of Embassy Tech Zone in Rajiv Gandhi InfoTech Park in the second phase of Hinjewadi development layout.

news.title: Gurugram: 52 owners booked for providing accommodation to foreigners without verification
news.para: According to officials, those who provide accommodation to foreigners must submit the details of the residing foreigner in Form C to the Registration authorities within 24 hours of the arrival of the foreigner at their premises. This helps the registration authorities in locating and tracking the foreigners.

news.title: UltraTech to cross 200 MTPA capacity by FY27 with acquisitions, expansion: Chairman
news.para: UltraTech last month announced acquisition of Tamil Nadu-based India Cements Ltd (ICL). Its Rs 3,142 crore open offer for acquiring 26 per cent stake will tentatively open on September 19.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates net loss widens to Rs 1,023 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: The total income rose to Rs 1,770.66 crore in April-June this fiscal from Rs 1,505.23 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: EFC (I) net profit jumps to Rs 16 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 105.28 crore in the April-June quarter of this fiscal year from Rs 57.04 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Shriram Properties' profit rises 5% to Rs 17.46 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 210.90 crore in the April-June period of this fiscal from Rs 157.17 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: KSH INFRA to invest Rs 450 crore to develop industrial & logistics park in Hosur
news.para: The park will cover approximately 50 acres of land and offer a development potential of 1.25 million sq ft. It is expected to generate employment for over 1,800 people.

news.title: Germany: PBB's profit plunges 74% in Q2 2024
news.para: PBB in recent years bet heavily on the U.S. market by offering commercial real estate loans, which across the industry have succumbed to pressure from high office vacancies and falling property prices following rises in interest rates and a trend towards home-working since the pandemic.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM directs officials to formulate plan to set up 100 industrial parks
news.para: ​​Instructing officials to initiate steps to attract industrialists to set up more parks, the CM noted that only 53 industrial parks exist in the state now.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to attach bank accounts of property tax defaulters
news.para: The Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) has gained new powers to recover property tax arrears by attaching the bank accounts of defaulters. With around three lakh properties on the tax default list, BBMP issued a notification allowing them to serve attachment warrants to banks and take action under Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita-2023 if banks fail to comply.
